ENTRY            30861   20251217   20260508   20260508       3222
SUBENT        30861001   20251217   20260508   20260508       3222
BIB                 13         25
TITLE      Isomeric yield ratio of 115m,gCd in the 116Cd(g,n) and
           116Cd(n,2n) reactions
AUTHOR     (H.Naik, G.N.Kim, W.Y.Jang, T.H.Nguyen)
INSTITUTE  (3INDTRM,3KORKNU)
REFERENCE  (J,NIM/B,529,68,2022)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,3KORKRM) MC-50 cyclotron (KIRAMS)
INC-SOURCE (P-BE) The neutron beam was produced from the 9Be(p,n)
            reaction by hitting 35 and 45 MeV proton beams on a
            2 mm thick Be target.
INC-SPECT  (EN-RSL-HW) The neutron spectrum was characterized by
            MCNPX 2.6.0.
SAMPLE     Natural Cd foil
METHOD     (ACTIV) Irradiation for 60 min (200 nA)
           (GSPEC) Started after the cooling time (57-79 hour)
DETECTOR   (HPGE) Energy resolution of 1.8 keV FWHM at 1332.5 keV
            peak of 60Co and detection efficiency of 20% at 1332.5
            keV relative to 3 inch diameter x 3 inch length
            NaI(Tl) detector
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-T) Total uncertainty                 (4.15-10.64%)
           (ERR-S,2.,10.) Statistical uncertainty          (2-10%)
           (ERR-1) irradiation and cooling time            (~0.5%)
           (ERR-2) detection efficiency                      (~3%)
           (ERR-3) half-life of products, gamma-ray intensity(~2%)
STATUS     (APRVD) Approved by G.N.Kim (2026-01-14)
HISTORY    (20251217C) S.C.Yang
ENDBIB              25
COMMON               3          3
ERR-1      ERR-2      ERR-3
PER-CENT   PER-CENT   PER-CENT
0.5        3.         2.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           32
SUBENT        30861002   20251217   20260508   20260508       3222
BIB                  4          8
REACTION   (48-CD-116(N,2N)48-CD-115-M/G,,SIG/RAT,,SPA)
DECAY-DATA (48-CD-115-M,44.56D,DG,933.84,0.020) 11/2-
           (48-CD-115-G,53.46HR,DG,336.24,0.4502,
                                DG,527.90,0.2745) 1/2+
COMMENT    The cross section of the 114Cd(n,g) reaction is very
            low at higher neuron energy and it was not considered.
            (by H.Naik 2025-12-20)
STATUS     (TABLE,,H.Naik+,J,NIM/B,529,68,2022) Table 3
ENDBIB               8
